MongoDB stores data for the App
The data for your app will be stored in a MongoDB Atlas Cluster collection named exercises. Each document in the collection must have the following properties. All the properties are required.

Data Parameters
Property	Data Type	Comments
name	String	The name of the exercise.
reps	Number	The number of times the exercise was performed, or the distance. The value must be an integer greater than 0.
weight	Number	The amount of the weight used for the exercise. The value must be an integer equal to or greater than 0.
unit	String	The unit of measurement of the weight or the reps. Values are kgs,  lbs, and miles.
date	Date 	The date the exercise was performed. Specified as the ISO string for date and time. Set the default to Date.now.
_id	Object	
Unique ID is automatically assigned by MongoDB when a document is created.

Internally, MongoDB creates an instance of the class ObjectId. In HTTP requests and responses, its string representation is used.


